- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper describes a model-driven approach for developing web information systems and discusses the use of appropriate tooling for transforming models into complete systems. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a runnable application from a set of models, which involves computational aspects. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper covers data structure and user rights management in the web information system. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the page structure and workflow within the system, which involves designing for user interaction. 
- cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) is also a possible category as the paper discusses an agile modeling approach for developing web information systems.
